results.name: a(n) = n IMPL prime(n), where IMPL is the bitwise logical implication.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
program: a265885 n = n `bimpl` a000040 n where
bimpl p q = 2 * bimpl p' q' + if u <= v then 1 else 0
where (p', u) = divMod p 2; (q', v) = divMod q 2
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Dec 17 2015
